  "texts": [
    "Fourth, the space of actions the protagonist can take must have few paths to success, and/or those paths must be seen as having a low probability of success.",
    "Another factor related to suspense is the narratological theory of disparities of knowledge (Branigan, 2013).",
    "This framework proposes that readers and story characters can have different knowledge of the story world.",
    "When a character knows something that the reader doesn't know, the revelation of that information can invoke surprise in the reader.",
    "However, when the reader knows something that the story world characters don't know, and that knowledge is related to the protagonist's chances of a negative outcome, then the reader may feel suspense."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Another factor related to suspense is the narratological theory of disparities of knowledge (Branigan, 2013)."
  ]
